  MPL uses the \indexmpldef{strided_vector_layout} class:
  %
  \cxxverbatimsnippet[examples/mpi/mpl/vector.cxx]{vectormpl}
  %
  It is possible to to send containers by iterators
  %
  \cxxverbatimsnippet[examples/mpi/mpl/sendrange.cxx]{mplsendrange}
  %
  Non-contiguous iteratable objects can be send with a
  \indexmpldef{iterator_layout}:
  %
\begin{lstlisting}
std::list<int> v(20, 0);
mpl::iterator_layout<int> l(v.begin(), v.end());
comm_world.recv(&(*v.begin()), l, 0);
\end{lstlisting}
